   config, operator-supplied values, or extension points meant to run
   caller-provided code — argue AGAINST the finding unless the report shows an
   untrusted path reaching them.

5. **Falsification**: Spend at least one tool call trying to break this
   finding. What invariant, allocator behavior, post-check, product-surface
   fact, trust-boundary fact, or nearby guard might stop it from being
   reachable / exploitable? Where your own check stays inconclusive, say so
